# Supply Chain Readiness

Application: `{{ app.name }}`
Image: `{{ image }}`

This directory contains generated helper scripts for image supply-chain validation.
The scripts are intentionally local and inspectable. `k8s-forge` does not install tools, push images, sign images automatically, or generate secrets.

## Vulnerability Scan

{% if supplyChain.scan.enabled %}`scan-image.sh` uses Trivy to scan the image for known vulnerabilities.

```bash
./scan-image.sh
```

Severity threshold: `{{ severity_csv }}`.
{% else %}Image scanning is disabled in `app.yaml`.
{% endif %}

## SBOM

{% if supplyChain.sbom.enabled %}`generate-sbom.sh` uses Syft to generate a Software Bill of Materials.

```bash
./generate-sbom.sh
```

SBOM output: `{{ sbom_output }}`.
{% else %}SBOM generation is disabled in `app.yaml`.
{% endif %}

## Signing

{% if supplyChain.signing.enabled %}`sign-image.sh` and `verify-image.sh` use Cosign.

```bash
./sign-image.sh
./verify-image.sh
```

Cosign signing usually requires a registry-backed image reference. Local-only images may not be suitable for signing and verification.
{% else %}Cosign signing is disabled. This is the default for local labs because signing usually requires a registry-backed image reference and a keyless or key-based workflow.
{% endif %}

## Traceability Notes

{% if uses_latest %}The selected image uses the `latest` tag. This is convenient for labs but weak for traceability. Prefer immutable version tags or digests for supply-chain validation.
{% endif %}{% if not registry_backed %}The selected image does not look registry-backed. Local images can be scanned and inspected, but signing and verification workflows usually need a registry reference.
{% endif %}

## Required Tools

- Trivy for vulnerability scanning.
- Syft for SBOM generation.
- Cosign for signing and verification when enabled.

Run `k8s-forge doctor` to see which tools are available locally.
